    <title>RAY TRACING DEMO</title>
    <link href="http://luochenhuan.github.io/2017/04/21/2014-12-02-CGdemo/"/>
    <id>http://luochenhuan.github.io/2017/04/21/2014-12-02-CGdemo/</id>
    <published>2017-04-21T09:24:08.000Z</published>
    <updated>2017-04-21T09:24:08.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Objectives"><a href="#Objectives" class="headerlink" title="Objectives:"></a>Objectives:</h1><!--
* Add additional primitives, e.g. Cylinder, Cone.
* Add Cone Light Source.
* Texture Mapping.
* Bump Mapping.
* Perlin Noise.
* Anti-aliasing by super-sampling.
* Refraction.
* Use multi-thread concurrent flow to improve the
* tracing.
* Use Hierarchical Bounding Boxes to improve the
* tracing.
* A nice scene of a room.

* Extra Objective: Soft Shadow
-->
<ul>
<li><a href="#obj1"> Add additional primitives</a></li>
<li><a href="#obj2"> Add Cone Light Source</a></li>
<li><a href="#obj3"> Texture Mapping</a></li>
<li><a href="#obj4"> Bump Mapping</a></li>
<li><a href="#obj5"> Perlin Noise</a></li>
<li><a href="#obj6"> Anti-aliasing by super-sampling</a></li>
<li><a href="#obj7"> Refraction</a></li>
<li><a href="#obj8"> Use multi-thread concurrent flow to imporve the tracing</a></li>
<li><a href="#obj9"> Use Hierarchical Bounding Boxes to imporve the tracing</a></li>
<li><a href="#obj10"> A nice scene of a room</a></li>
<li><a href="#obj11"> Extra Objective: Soft Shadow</a></li>
</ul>
<p><a id="obj1"></a></p>
<h2 id="1-Additional-primitives"><a href="#1-Additional-primitives" class="headerlink" title="1. Additional primitives"></a>1. Additional primitives</h2><p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/primitives_zpsa6dcd6ae.png" alt="primitives-example"></p>
<p><a id="obj2"></a></p>
<h2 id="2-Cone-Light-Source"><a href="#2-Cone-Light-Source" class="headerlink" title="2. Cone Light Source"></a>2. Cone Light Source</h2><p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/conelight_test_0_zpsbe933d74.png" alt="conelight" style="width: 512px;"></p>
<p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/conelight_test_zps8f0cbc36.png" alt="conelight" style="width: 512px;"><br><a id="obj3"></a></p>
<h2 id="3-Texture-Mapping"><a href="#3-Texture-Mapping" class="headerlink" title="3. Texture Mapping"></a>3. Texture Mapping</h2><p>I use image textures for the first sphere and the second cylinder. Checker patterns can be created by arbitrary number of squares per row and per column. The texture for the third cylinder is generated by <code>perlin noise</code>.<br>(The last row is use for Bump Mapping.)</p>
<p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/texture_show_2_zps393d3482.png" alt="tm" style="width: 512px;"></p>
<p><a id="obj4"></a></p>
<h2 id="4-Bump-Mapping"><a href="#4-Bump-Mapping" class="headerlink" title="4. Bump Mapping"></a>4. Bump Mapping</h2><p>As shown above, primitives of the last row use <code>normal maps</code> as follows, as well as the wall behind:</p>
<p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/stone_normalmap_zps1387148a.png" style="float: left; width: 45%; margin-right: 1%; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/brick_nm_zpsa8ea27e5.png" style="float: left; width: 45%; margin-right: 1%; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"></p>
<p style="clear: both;">

</p><p>The third and forth spheres use the same materials, but the forth one have uneven surface due to normal mapping.<br>To simulate the uneven texture of brick walls, I use Perlin Noise to turbulence the surface normal of objects.</p>
<p>In the right image, the upper sphere and the wall use bump mapping.</p>
<p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/non_perlin_show_zpscdb917ed.png" style="float: left; width: 45%; margin-right: 1%; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/perlin_show_zpsb7fea875.png" style="float: left; width: 45%; margin-right: 1%; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"></p>
<p style="clear: both;">

</p><p><a id="obj5"></a></p>
<h2 id="5-Perlin-Noise"><a href="#5-Perlin-Noise" class="headerlink" title="5. Perlin Noise"></a>5. Perlin Noise</h2><p>In Bump Mapping, we see the normal turbulence created by Perlin Noise.</p>
<p>Here I also create 4 textures from Perlin Noise.<br><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/perlin_show_zps30e2fd22.png" alt="Perlin-example"></p>
<p><a id="obj6"></a></p>
<h2 id="6-Anti-aliasing-by-super-sampling"><a href="#6-Anti-aliasing-by-super-sampling" class="headerlink" title="6. Anti-aliasing by super-sampling"></a>6. Anti-aliasing by super-sampling</h2><p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/perlin_show_aa_zps594127c2.png" alt="wall-example"><br><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/refract_show_aa_zps51d1dbaf.png" alt="refract-example"><br><a id="obj7"></a></p>
<h2 id="7-Refraction"><a href="#7-Refraction" class="headerlink" title="7. Refraction"></a>7. Refraction</h2><p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/refract_show_2_zpsab28ae4d.png" alt="refr" style="width: 512px;"></p>
<p><a id="obj8"></a></p>
<h2 id="8-Use-multi-thread-concurrent-flow-to-improve-the-tracing"><a href="#8-Use-multi-thread-concurrent-flow-to-improve-the-tracing" class="headerlink" title="8. Use multi-thread concurrent flow to improve the tracing"></a>8. Use multi-thread concurrent flow to improve the tracing</h2><p>For macho-cow.lua(128x128) in A4,</p>
<p>thread=1 : 19min</p>
<p>thread=2 : 8min</p>
<p>thread=4 : 3min</p>
<p>For final scene without chair.obj(256x256),</p>
<p>thread=1 : 80s</p>
<p>thread=2 : 76s</p>
<p>thread=4 : 66s</p>
<p><a id="obj9"></a></p>
<h2 id="9-Use-Hierarchical-Bounding-Boxes-to-improve-the-tracing"><a href="#9-Use-Hierarchical-Bounding-Boxes-to-improve-the-tracing" class="headerlink" title="9. Use Hierarchical Bounding Boxes to improve the tracing"></a>9. Use Hierarchical Bounding Boxes to improve the tracing</h2><p>For hier.lua(512x512) in A4,</p>
<p>HBB : 9sec</p>
<p>BB : 19sec</p>
<p>I only draw out geometry nodes above threshold depth.</p>
<p>Threshold depth = 2:</p>
<p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/hier_aa_zps20879dcb.png" style="float: left; width: 45%; margin-right: 1%; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/hier_bb_zpsab9711fe.png" style="float: left; width: 45%; margin-right: 1%; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"></p>
<p style="clear: both;">


</p><p>Threshold depth = 3:</p>
<p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/self_zps7af4ba8e.png" style="float: left; width: 45%; margin-right: 1%; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/self_3_zps37961674.png" style="float: left; width: 45%; margin-right: 1%; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"></p>
<p style="clear: both;">


</p><p><a id="obj11"></a></p>
<h2 id="Extra-Soft-Shadow"><a href="#Extra-Soft-Shadow" class="headerlink" title="Extra. Soft Shadow"></a>Extra. Soft Shadow</h2><p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/refract_show_ss_zpsd762c423.png" alt="refr" style="width: 512px;"></p>
<p><a id="obj10"></a></p>
<h2 id="10-A-nice-scene-of-a-room"><a href="#10-A-nice-scene-of-a-room" class="headerlink" title="10. A nice scene of a room"></a>10. A nice scene of a room</h2><p>1024*1024 total time = 100min with:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>32 threads</p>
</li>
<li><p>HBB</p>
</li>
<li><p>super sampling of 8 neighbors</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><img src="http://i98.photobucket.com/albums/l265/Haiyu_Zhen/CS488/final_1024_zpsfb3ca9c1.png" alt="final-example"></p>
]]></content>
    
